--- body ---
## Context

Ticket 0028 added `extract_pdf_metadata()` which reads `/Title`, `/Author`,
and XMP fields from a PDF's embedded metadata. The function exists and is
tested but is **not called from the pipeline** — it is dead production code.

QA of all 215 PDFs in the ArchiveCCS corpus (2026-04-29) found the embedded
metadata is almost universally garbage for this kind of grey literature:

- Titles are Word filenames: `Microsoft Word - TKC Risk Paper final_worddoc.doc`
- Authors are internal usernames: `spc`, `gb05`, `Klaas`, `ddesmicht`, `i07potti`
- Some have conference slugs instead of paper titles: `GHGT-9_Chiavari`

Only a handful of records (e.g. Elsevier journals like Ashworth et al.) had
real, usable title and author values in their embedded metadata.

**Current situation:** `extract_pdf_metadata` is never invoked from `pipeline.py`.
No garbage is reaching item fields. The risk is zero until someone wires it in.

## Decision needed

Three options:

**A. Delete it.** The function is dead code; the metadata it extracts is
not trustworthy for grey literature. Keep only `extract_first_page` and
`extract_doi_from_first_page`.

**B. Keep it, wire it to LLM context only (0015).** Pass embedded metadata as
additional evidence to the LLM resolver prompt — the LLM can judge whether
the title looks like a Word filename or a real title. Never write it to
item fields directly.

**C. Keep it, wire it with a quality filter.** Heuristically reject garbage
values (filename extensions, all-lowercase, very short, no spaces) before
writing to item fields.

Recommendation: **B**. The LLM is better placed to judge metadata quality
than a heuristic filter. Option A loses potentially useful signal for the
LLM. Option C adds complexity and will fail on edge cases.

## Actions

1. Decide between A, B, C with the user.
2. If B: wire `extract_pdf_metadata` result into the LLM resolver context
   dict in ticket 0015 — no extra ticket needed.
3. If A: delete `extract_pdf_metadata`, `_extract_info_dict`, `_extract_xmp_meta`,
   `_xmp_scalar`, `_XMP_ATTR_MAP`, `_INFO_KEY_MAP` from `pdf.py`, and remove
   `test_pdf_metadata.py` entirely.

## Exit criteria

- Decision documented in this ticket's log.
- Code consistent with the decision.
